VGADISK Version 1.0: 176K virtual disk in VGA memory    (c) 1991 Tommy Frandsen
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FEATURES:
     - 176K virtual disk (RAM disk) using only VGA memory
     - Is compatible with all text-only programs
     - Easy installation and use
     - Has been tested on many different machines

REQUIREMENTS:
     - An IBM PC/XT/AT/PS2/Clone
     - MS-DOS/PC-DOS 2.0 or higher
     - A VGA graphics adaptor

SUPPLIED FILES:
     - VGADISK.SYS: Device driver for the virtual disk
     - VGADISK.EXE: Use when running graphics programs 
     - VGADISK.DOC: Documentation (this file)

INSTALLATION: 
     - Copy VGADISK.SYS into the root directory of your boot disk
     - Insert the line "DEVICE=VGADISK.SYS" in CONFIG.SYS
     - Reboot by pressing CTRL-ALT-DEL or by turning OFF/ON
     - You should see a message containing the drive designation of
       the created virtual disk (typically D: or E:)
     - The virtual disk is now ready to be used as a normal DOS disk

COMPATIBILITY:
     - VGADISK is compatible with any program that doesn't use graphics
     - Graphics programs will destroy the contents of the virtual disk
     - The virtual disk can be used like a normal (very fast) DOS disk

VGADISK.EXE:
     - Allows you to restore the virtual disk after running graphics programs
     - "VGADISK -F"    : Reformat the virtual disk 
     - "VGADISK -Sxxx" : Save an image of the virtual disk to file xxx
     - "VGADISK -Lxxx" : Load an image of the virtual disk from file xxx
     - Example (could be included in a BAT-file):
          VGADISK -SC:\TMP (save the virtual disk to file C:\TMP)
          FS4              (run Flight Simulator or a similar program)
	  VGADISK -LC:\TMP (load the virtual disk from file C:\TMP)

WARNINGS:
     - If you fail to restore the virtual disk after running a graphics 
       program, the results of using the virtual disk are unpredictable.
